<br>
Also, I probably won't care about what anyone has to say, but might be willing to clarify some things, if necessary.  Although some clarifications are none of anyone's business outside of Dreadstorm's members, who've all heard what I have to say, and thus won't be responded to/clarified <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
OK, so it essentially boils down to the fact that my membership in Dreadstorm hasn't been fun for a fair amount of time.  My role has diminished largely, from an active, important role to one that pretty much anyone could do (main raid tank to generic unmezzable add tank).  With this change in role, which came about VERY suddenly and with no warning, I've felt diminished importance, recognition, and respect from the guild at large (although this is certainly unintended, it is none the less what I've felt).  I believe that DS won't feel <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>too</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> heavy a loss without me, and that it won't affect the guild on a large scale.<br>
<br>
There have also been very considerable advancements in the achievements of Dreadstorm in the past few weeks, which has brought a change of attitude to some of the membership - some people have been asking for more raiding and guild raid participation.  I'm not opposed to raiding - in fact, I would like to see more than I have with Dreadstorm.  However, I disagree with the highly pro-raid sentiments some members have; I feel they oppose the guild's original vision/purpose - to be a CASUAL high-end raiding guild.  I respect the guild and its intentions, so I will look to see more and varied raiding and high-end activities elsewhere on the server.  (As a side note, I've been considering this course of action for a while and feel that now is a fair enough time to move on, for both me and DS).<br>
<br>
There are a number of minor, specific things that can be groupped with the ones above, but they aren't really important to the big picture.<br>
<br>
As to what I'll do now, I'm not sure on any specifics.  I'm hoping to spend time raiding with both Resolution and Fire and Fury, to determine which, if either, best fits my intrests and expectations.  I don't mean to insult either guild, only to try and make the best decision now, to lessen/eliminate problems that might appear down the line.<br>
<br>
Once again, this isn't a big deal and no part intended as a flame.  This post is only really here because I'm too lazy to explain to every single person who asks me about it.  If you think it (as a whole or some specific part) is a big deal for some reason, please ask me in game and discuss it there.<br>
<br>
And for people who just troll these boards looking for crap to bitch about, I'll try not to disappoint - I made this nice new sig pic so you can bitch and while all you want! :P<br>
